{
  "stem": "18281.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then those people were transported by cattle cars, just like the Germans did, to southern France, to Saint Cyprien, where I had-- on the way down, somebody had marked the traitors, spies, on the cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And Senegalese troops started burning one of the cattle cars and shot into them, trying to kill those traitors.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They were 90% Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Some of the guys died in those trains.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they finally reached this camp that had been used to sort out the Spaniards when they crossed the border in Saint Cyprien.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was built on sand.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the toilets were elevated like watchtowers with a barrel under them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And my dad had a book with him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And this book became-- every page could be sold.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That was like gold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But I also know that you had to duck.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Instead of going into the barrels, those pieces of paper were flying all over the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And you really had to duck in order not to get hit by one of the papers that had been used.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Eventually with my uncle, who also was in that camp-- by the way, Erika's dad was in that camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He wasn't freed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He escaped with fake papers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They went to Perpignan the next town in France.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- my uncle was-- obtained the permit to go back home because his wife was a Belgian.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then they went into a bank.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they faked the papers, saying that he was allowed to be in the company of my dad.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And That paper is in the wall of the Holocaust Memorial in Montreal.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, again, I brought home a paycheck from that metal work where I worked.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's really all we had.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Belgium, the Germans didn't really bother with the Jews till 1942.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
